<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>It's based almost entirely on level as far as I can tell</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?TheBlack[BCK]">TheBlack[BCK]</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 2:39 p.m. 12/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> It's based almost entirely on level as far as I can tell<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=805" TARGET=_self>Magic Resistance</A> (Raven De'Vine)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>If you are a level higher than your opponent then you resist most spells. The greater the difference in level, the harder it is to effect your target with a spell. Some spells are exceptions to this rule, as I understand it there is a low level Necro spell (maybe blood boil) that tends to ignore resistance. This is one of the *B*G* problem areas for PvP combat in EQ that needs to be addressed by Verant.
<P>&gt; Is it true you gain Magic Resistance (MR) with each level? That
<BR>&gt; just doesn't make any sense to me. If thats true, what reason
<BR>&gt; would you have for NOT playing some type of warrior class?
<BR>&gt; Warrior classes are allready supplemented with higher hit points
<BR>&gt; at each level so they can afford to take more magical damage.
<BR>&gt; Factor in MR and warrior classes eat magic classes alive.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
